  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nIf switch the application to dark mode, having the device in light mode (or vice versa), then after reopening the application the existing chats will disappear from the Home screen.\r\nTo display chats again, need to switch to another tab and reopen the Home screen.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nChats don't disappear \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/114709396-d0ac3280-9d2c-11eb-8392-f3326ae8cb3e.mp4\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n**Precondition:** there are some chats on the Home screen\r\n\r\n- Set dark mode in device settings\r\n- Open Status \r\n- `Profile` > `Appearance` > Set `Light mode`\r\n- Close app\r\n- Reopen Status > Check the chat list\r\n- Navigate to another tab\r\n- Go back to Home screen > Check the chat list\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: Nightly 14/04\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS",
